Preconditions:
The input `points` array must not be null.
The input `points` array must have a length greater than or equal to Each element in the `points` array must be an array of length 2, representing the x and y coordinates of a point.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the width of the widest vertical area between two points.
The returned width should be such that no points are inside the area.
If there are multiple widest vertical areas, the method should return the width of any one of them.